snippet.textDisplay:
For the first time in thirty years, we have a squad of players that ranks with our greatest ever squads.
.....and individual players that we can put alongside,....and some even above,....... what we consider our greatest ever.
Ray Clemence is regarded as our number one keeper of all time, even Brucie plays second fiddle to him, but now, all that is stopping Ally The Cat from taking the shirt off him is success....trophy's...phil neal was a player l thought was forever going to be our greatest ever right= back, Trent has seen to that.
Alan Hanson is regarded as the best centre back that ever pulled on our red jersey...l think Van is better!.
Hendo is already going toe to toe with evey red midfielder from Molby, McMahon, and Jimmy Caae and only success is stopping him from being better than Souness.
Firminho is the same class as Dalglish..( I nevee thought l would ever say that ! )
Mane is better than 'nailed on' John Barnes...and name me any former player...inc Rush, Keegan and Fowler you would swap for Salah. And of course....the way things are going, Klopp is destined to sit side by side with Shanks.
Merry xmas reds.
And a fkng brilliant new yr.
YNWA
